results.task_name: Break down a feature into tasks
results.prompt_sent: I need to implement user notifications for workunit updates. Think about what steps are actually needed to build this end-to-end, then create a workunit called "Implement User Notifications" and add all the implementation tasks to it. Be thorough — this is a real feature, not a toy example.

arguments.name: Implement User Notifications
arguments.problem_statement: Currently, users are not notified when workunits they are involved in (e.g., assigned to, mentioned in, or subscribed to) undergo significant changes such as status updates, priority changes, task completions, or new comments. This leads to delays in response times and reduced collaboration efficiency.
arguments.success_criteria: Users receive timely notifications via email and/or in-app alerts for key workunit events (status change, priority change, task completion, comment added). Notifications must be configurable per user (opt-in/out per channel), reliable (delivered within 5 minutes of event), and support at least 10K concurrent users without degradation.
arguments.description: Build a robust notification system for workunit updates that delivers timely, configurable alerts to users via email and in-app channels. This includes event detection, user preference handling, message templating, queueing, and delivery infrastructure.
